main event: A round, brilliant object like a bright star was observed close overhead before turning and passing out in Monroe, Wisconsin on March 29, 1960.
interesting points: The object was possibly a balloon, as it moved erratically and appeared to carry the balloon around like a toy.
The object was observed for about 2 minutes.
The sighting occurred at night, with clear weather conditions and good visibility.
A jet aircraft was observed flying above the sighting location, but it was not correlated with the UFO.
No physical evidence or photographs were available to further investigate the sighting.
sighted object: A round, brilliant object like a bright star
witnesses: Stephen M. Flanagan, Capt., USAF and L.R. Rambler, Night Watchman
